4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under current law, the Alabama G.I. Dependent
6 Scholarship Program provides scholarships to eligible
7 dependents of disabled and deceased veterans that meet
8 certain residency and disability requirements.
9 This bill would reduce the minimum disability
10 rating for participation in the program for a disabled
11 veteran to 30 percent.
12 This bill would also establish a pilot program
13 to allow a certain number of dependents of eligible
14 veterans to participate in the scholarship
15 program.
16
17
18 A BILL
19 TO BE ENTITLED
20 AN ACT
21
22 Related to the Alabama G.I. Dependent Scholarship
23 Program; to amend Sections 31-6-4, 31-6-6, and 31-6-9, Code of
24 Alabama 1975; to reduce the minimum disability rating required
25 for participation in the program; and to establish a pilot
26 program to admit additional dependents of certain disabled
27 veterans into the scholarship program.
28 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
Page 1

BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
SB224 INTRODUCED
